message: /* Personal life */According to Wikipedia's page on verifiability (https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability), it states "Please immediately remove contentious material about living people that is unsourced or poorly sourced.". As the phrase "neither of which are approved treatments for the disease" has no sourcing whatsoever related to whether or not these treatments are approved or unapproved, I must remove it. If you have an issue with Wikipedia, take it up with them but they...

/* Personal life */Even though someone sourced it, it's still not relevant and bloats the article.\nWikipedia states that "Material that is irrelevant or out of scope to an article's topic can unnecessarily bloat an article, making it difficult for a reader to remain focused, and can also give the material undue weight. Directness of relevance is an important measure and consideration." This section is not meant to debate the effectiveness of treatment, but to simply state that West had covid
/* Personal life */ Quotation from the cited article: "He said he was taking hydroxychloroquine and ivermectin -- two drugs that do not have a proven track record of success in treating Covid-19."
Undid revision 1067395468 by [[Special:Contributions/Hutch.20|Hutch.20]] ([[User talk:Hutch.20|talk]]) properly sourced, and no opposition except for meat/sock puppets
